    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nDescribe the problem (concisely).\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean -u a.lua`, then type `:s/abc<c-h><c-h><c-h>`\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({})\nvim.keymap.set(\"c\", \"<c-h>\", function()\n\tvim.fn.setcmdline(vim.fn.getcmdline():sub(1, -2))\n    -- workaround: vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(vim.keycode('<c-r><c-r><c-r>') 'nt', false)\nend)\n\n```\nNote `<c-h>` won't refresh cmdline\n\n## Expected behavior\nCmdline should be updated immediately\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.13.0-dev-68 gb64d96ed8d` neovim/neovim@b64d96ed8d\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.10-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
